<TITLE> Man Utd go top after 1-0 win over Liverpool </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LIVERPOOL, England, Dec 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Manchester United overtook Arsenal at the top of the Premier League on Sunday after Carlos Tevez's first-half strike gave them a 1-0 win at Liverpool. Arsenal, two points behind United, have the chance to make a quick return to top spot when they host third-placed Chelsea at 1600 GMT. United winger Ryan Giggs drilled a corner to Wayne Rooney, whose shot was flicked into the top of the net by an unmarked Tevez in the 43rd minute to break the deadlock in a first half where Liverpool had the better chances. Rooney missed a great chance to stretch United's lead with less than a quarter of an hour to go but sent the ball wide after Ryan Babel had gone close for Liverpool a minute before
